ne and The Only: Perspectives on the Development of a Divine Concept -- tGod and His People: The Concept of Kingship and Cult in the Ancient Near East -- tYHWH in the Northern and Southern Kingdom -- tFrom Many Gods to the One God: The Archaeological Evidence -- tMonotheism and Angelology in Daniel -- tJustice, the King and the Gods: Polytheism and Emerging Monotheism in the Ancient World -- tBackmatter0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDie jüngere archäologische und bibelwissenschaftliche Forschung stellt das traditionelle Bild der Geschichte des antiken Israel infrage.Der vorliegende Band führt neueste Forschungsergebnisse beider Wissenschaftsdisziplinen zusammen und stellt die Frage nach der historischen Faktizität oder literarischen Fiktionalität des Davidisch-Salomonischen Großreichs (‛One Nation’) und der Kultreformmaßnahme unter Josia (‛One Cult’). Die politischen und kulturellen Wechselbeziehungen innerhalb des Vorderen Orients werden am Beispiel der antiken Stadt Beth She'an/Scythopolis veranschaulicht und in ihrer Bedeutung für den Wandel des Gottesbildes (‛One God’) problematisiert.Der Sammelband enthält siebzehn englischsprachige Beiträge von international anerkannten Forschern aus Israel, Finnland und Deutschland.  aRecent archaeological and biblical research challenges the traditional view of the history of ancient Israel. This book presents the latest findings of both academic disciplines regarding the United Monarchy of David and Solomon (‛One Nation’) and the cult reform under Josiah (‛One Cult’), raising the issue of fact versus fiction. The political and cultural interrelations in the Near East are illustrated on the example of the ancient city of Beth She'an/Scythopolis and are discussed as to their significance for the transformation in the conception of God (‛One God’). The volume contains 17 contributions by internationally eminent scholars from Israel, Finland and Germany.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zIsrael. 4aAltes Testament. 4aBeth Shean. 4aBiblische Archäologie. 4aGotteskonzepte. 4aKult. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aBeth She'an.  aBiblical Archaeology.  aCult.  aDivine Concepts.  aOld Testament.1 aAuffarth, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlum, Erhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorzilius, Björn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinkelstein, Israel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerzog, Ze\x27ev, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeyden, Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKratz, Reinhard G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKratz, Reinhard G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKöckert, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMazar, Amihai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMazor, Gabriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPakkala, Juha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPilger, Tanja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRofé, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchaudig, Hanspeter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSegal, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpieckermann, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpieckermann, Herman